        <h1>ELH Bash example</h1>
        <p>Runs the following Bash script on the server, similar to PHP</p>
        <pre><code>
    fruits <gra>=</gra> <dar>[</dar><gre>"apple"</gre><dar>,</dar> <gre>"banana"</gre><dar>,</dar> <gre>"cherry"</gre><dar>]</dar>
    fruits<dar>.<blu>each</blu> <pur>do</pur> |<red>fruit</red>|</dar>
        <blu>puts</blu> <gre>"&lt;p&gt;I like</gre> <pin>#{</pin>fruit<pin>}</pin><gre>.&lt;/p&gt;"</gre>
    <pur>end</pur>
        </code></pre>
        <h2>The output:</h2>
        <$ruby
            fruits = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"]
            fruits.each do |fruit|
                puts "<p>I like #{fruit}.</p>"
            end
        $>
    </body>
